<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-19T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="612" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/452</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-19T13:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Bethlehem Steel Company advise Department of report from its manager that
                            anti-American feeling very strong among rebels, that the mines are
                            practically without adequate protection as marines are kept constantly
                            moving and that Cuban Government cannot end trouble without substantial
                            assistance.</p>
                        <p>You will communicate this information to President Menocal and ascertain
                            why ample and permanent protection is not furnished these properties.
                            Report by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>